2) RDD with simulated model¶

We generate the simulated data points. For each age $a$ (in years) between 25 and 39, we define $Y$ as the average employment rate between $a$ and $a+1$.

In [7]:
let
age_grid = (25:39) *12
Y = [quadgk(x->1-sum(unemp.real(x)[:]),a,a+12,atol=1e-8)[1]/12 for a in age_grid] ## equivalent to ERC in LM2008

table = zeros(5)

#explaining variables
TREAT = [a>=canada.A for a in age_grid]
consta = ones(size(age_grid))
age1 = collect(age_grid)
age2 = age1 .^2
age3 = age1 .^3
age1_spl = (age1 .- canada.A) .* TREAT 
age2_spl = (age1 .- canada.A).^2 .* TREAT 

# linear
X = hcat(TREAT, consta, age1)
beta = inv(X' * X) * (X' * Y)
table[1] = beta[1]

# quadratic
X = hcat(TREAT, consta, age1, age2)
beta = inv(X' * X) * (X' * Y)
table[2] = beta[1]

# cubic
X = hcat(TREAT, consta, age1, age2, age3)
beta = inv(X' * X) * (X' * Y)
table[3] = beta[1]

# linear spline
X = hcat(TREAT, consta, age1, age1_spl )
beta = inv(X' * X) * (X' * Y)
table[4] = beta[1]

# quadratic spline
X = hcat(TREAT, consta, age1, age2, age1_spl, age2_spl)
beta = inv(X' * X) * (X' * Y)
table[5] = beta[1]

## RDD estimates from the data on the left
display(hcat([-0.041, -0.051, -0.048, -0.049, -0.056 ] ,table))
end

3) Discussion¶

The role of $m$ and $q$

In [10]:
## function to evaluate bias for given parameters
function whatbias(;m=canada.m, q0=canada.q0, qa=canada.qa, Aret=canada.Aret, ξ=canada.ξ)
    age_grid = (25:39) *12
    newC = update_Country1(α=canada.α, m=m, q0=q0, qa=qa, Aret=Aret, ξ=ξ)
    newV =  find_Surplus(newC)
    newunemp = find_Unemp(newV, newC) 

    ## RDD estimate 
    Y = [quadgk(x->1-sum(newunemp.real(x)[:]),a,a+12)[1]/12 for a in age_grid] ## equivalent to ERC in LM2008
    TREAT = [a>=canada.A for a in age_grid]
    consta = ones(size(age_grid))
    age1 = collect(age_grid)
    age1_spl = (age1 .- canada.A) .* TREAT 
    X = hcat(TREAT, consta, age1, age1_spl )
    beta = inv(X' * X) * (X' * Y)
    RDDestimate = beta[1]

    ## LATE
    emp_after = 1-sum(newunemp.with(newC.A)[:])
    emp_before = 1-sum(newunemp.without(newC.A)[:])
    LATE = emp_after-emp_before
    return (RDDestimate, LATE)
end

## get datapoints for the 3D graph
Ndata = 400 #400
logscale = 2
data3D = zeros(Ndata^2,5)
i0 = 0
selecX = []
selecY = []
mdec_vec = vcat(range(-1,stop=0,length=Integer(Ndata/2)),range(0.001,stop=1,length=Integer(Ndata/2)))
qdec_vec = vcat(range(-1,stop=0,length=Integer(Ndata/2)),range(0.001,stop=1,length=Integer(Ndata/2)))
i=0
@time for mdec in mdec_vec, qdec in qdec_vec
    i +=1
    newm = canada.m*logscale^mdec
    newq0 = canada.q0*logscale^qdec
    (RDDestimate, LATE) = whatbias(m=newm, q0=newq0)

    data3D[i,:] = [mdec, qdec, -RDDestimate, -LATE , RDDestimate-LATE] 
    if (mdec == 0) & (newq0 <= canada.q0 )
        push!(selecY, i)
    end
    if (qdec == 0) & (newm >= canada.m )
        push!(selecX, i)
    end
    if (mdec == 0) & (qdec == 0)
        i0 = i
    end
end

## table of bias
makerow(text, RDD, LATE) = [text round(RDD,digits=3) round(LATE,digits=3) round((RDD-LATE)/(abs(LATE))*100,digits=1)]
function makerow(text::String, wb)
    (RDD, LATE) = wb
    println("The estimate and LATE $text are $RDD and $LATE")
    return makerow(text, RDD, LATE) 
end

mytab = DataFrame(makerow("in the calibrated model", whatbias()), :auto)

end

for xi in 0.25:0.25:1

## bias if we use job-finding rates
function average_JFR(a::Float64, uvec, Svec, C::Country1)
    num = uvec[1] * JFR(Svec[1], C) + uvec[2] * JFR(Svec[2], C) 
    den = sum(uvec)
    return num/den
end

function whatbias_JFR(;m=canada.m, q0=canada.q0, qa=canada.qa, Aret=canada.Aret, ξ=canada.ξ)
    age_grid = (25:39)*12
    newC = update_Country1(α=canada.α, m=m, q0=q0, qa=qa, Aret=Aret, ξ=ξ)
    newV =  find_Surplus(newC)
    newunemp = find_Unemp(newV, newC) 

    ## RDD estimate 
    auxfun = a -> a>canada.A ? average_JFR(a, newunemp.real(a), newV.Σ(a), newC) : average_JFR(a, newunemp.real(a), newV.S(a), newC) 
    #Y = [auxfun(a) for a in 12. * age_grid]
    Y = [quadgk(auxfun,a,a+12)[1]/12 for a in age_grid]
    TREAT = [a>=canada.A for a in age_grid]
    consta = ones(size(age_grid))
    age1 = collect(age_grid)
    age1_spl = (age1 .- canada.A) .* TREAT 
    X = hcat(TREAT, consta, age1, age1_spl )
    beta = inv(X' * X) * (X' * Y)
    RDDestimate = beta[1]

    ## LATE
    emp_after = average_JFR(newC.A, newunemp.with(newC.A), newV.Σ(newC.A), newC)
    emp_before = average_JFR(newC.A, newunemp.without(newC.A), newV.Ψ(newC.A), newC)
    LATE = emp_after-emp_before
    return (RDDestimate, LATE)
end

JFR_after = average_JFR(canada.A, unemp.real(canada.A), V.Σ(canada.A), canada)
boteRDD(RDD_JFR ,LATE_JFR) = JFR_after/(JFR_after+canada.q0) - (JFR_after-RDD_JFR)/(JFR_after-RDD_JFR+canada.q0) 
function makerow_JFR(text, wb)
    println("$text")
    (RDD ,LATE) = whatbias()
    (RDD_JFR ,LATE_JFR) = wb
    println("When considering the average JFR, the RDD estimate and LATE are $RDD_JFR and $LATE_JFR")
    bote = boteRDD(RDD_JFR ,LATE_JFR)
    println("Back-of-the-envelope calculation give and RDD on employment at $bote")
    # push!(mytab, )
    println("If the RDD was right, we would obtain ", JFR_after/(JFR_after+canada.q0) - (JFR_after-LATE_JFR)/(JFR_after-LATE_JFR+canada.q0) )
    return makerow(text, bote, LATE) 
end
